## Lemonade Server Development

When Lemonade Server is running, both the embedding and transcription pipelines are
fully operational:

```bash
# Start Lemonade (separate terminal)
lemonade-server serve

# Verify
curl http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health

# Pull models
lemonade-server pull embed-gemma-300m-FLM        # embeddings (NPU, 0.62 GB) — default
lemonade-server pull bge-reranker-v2-m3-GGUF     # reranking (GPU/CPU) — used by cli_demo
lemonade-server pull whisper-v3-turbo-FLM        # transcription (NPU, 1.55 GB)

# Point u-forge.ai at it (optional — localhost:13305 is auto-discovered)
export LEMONADE_URL="http://localhost:13305/api/v1"
```

**Standard GPU/CPU embedding:** Any llamacpp embedding model with the `embeddings`
label in the catalog is eligible. The model is selected by preference list in
`ModelConfig.embedding_model_preferences`. Standard embeddings use a 768-dim vector
space (e.g. `embed-gemma-300m-FLM`). High-quality embeddings use 4096-dim models
(e.g. `Qwen3-Embedding-8B-GGUF`). Do not mix models from incompatible spaces.

**Server URL resolution** (`lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url()`):
1. `GET http://localhost:13305/api/v1/health` (2 s timeout)
2. `GET http://127.0.0.1:13305/api/v1/health`
3. `LEMONADE_URL` environment variable — accepted as-is, no liveness check

Setting `LEMONADE_URL` is therefore **optional** when Lemonade Server is running on
its default port. If no server can be found at all, a descriptive error is returned —
there is no silent local fallback.

```rust
// Discover catalog and build a provider
let url = lemonade::resolve_lemonade_url().await
    .ok_or_else(|| anyhow!("No Lemonade Server found"))?;
let catalog = LemonadeServerCatalog::discover(&url).await?;
let selector = ModelSelector::new(catalog, config.models.clone());

// Construct embedding providers
for sel in selector.select_embedding_models() {
    let p = ProviderFactory::build(&sel, Capability::Embedding, &url, 10, None).await?;
    // register with InferenceQueueBuilder
}

// For STT/LLM that share the GPU, pass the shared gpu_mgr
let gpu_mgr = Arc::new(GpuResourceManager::new());
let p = ProviderFactory::build(&llm_sel, Capability::TextGeneration, &url, 100, Some(Arc::clone(&gpu_mgr))).await?;
```

